      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">01</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Stratification — the cohort the system cannot see yet</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Abdul is in the cohort the in-clinic system finds last. Mid-30s, in work, no symptoms yet, family history of cardiovascular disease. The 4.2 million adults in England with undiagnosed hypertension live in this cohort. The risk is real; the visibility is not. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="abdul-s1"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image">
          <div class="stage-image-icon">&#x1F4DD;</div>
          <div>Abdul &middot; act 1</div>
          <div class="stage-image-caption">illustration to follow &middot; stratification stage</div>
        </div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">I am 38 and I have never had a heart check in my life. My dad had his first MI at 51. The system was never going to find me.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Abdul</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What is happening</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">UKHSA and NHS Digital data show large cohorts of adults at cardiovascular risk who are not yet engaged with primary care for that reason. Stratification through age-band, postcode and family-history flags identifies the cohort before the symptoms do.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Wait until presentation — a chest pain, a stroke, an A&amp;E visit. The first contact with the system is the event the system was supposed to prevent.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">Who is in the loop</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Sarah&apos;s commissioner cohort analysis. Population health analysts. Public-health team identifying the at-risk cohort.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

