      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Treatment — the conversation the result triggers</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">The result shows raised cholesterol and an elevated cardiovascular risk score. The system routes the result to Abdul&apos;s GP, who picks up the conversation: lifestyle, possibly a statin. The treatment route is the same as it would be if the blood had come from a clinic. Only the venue changed. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="abdul-s4"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image">
          <div class="stage-image-icon">&#x1F4DD;</div>
          <div>Abdul &middot; act 4</div>
          <div class="stage-image-caption">illustration to follow &middot; treatment stage</div>
        </div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">The GP rang me. We talked about diet, exercise and the statin question. The conversation was the same conversation I would have had anyway. The blood draw just happened on my own time.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Abdul</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What is happening</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">The clinical interpretation, prescribing and follow-up remain with the patient&apos;s GP. The home pathway changes the data-capture venue, not the clinical-decision venue. NICE-guideline-aligned treatment thresholds and prescribing remain unchanged.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">A GP appointment to discuss a blood test that itself required a separate GP appointment. The conversation that mattered was always the same; the venue stack was the friction.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">Who is in the loop</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Abdul&apos;s GP. Practice pharmacist if a statin is prescribed. NICE guidelines.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

