        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">It is in the app now. I check the blood-pressure thing every couple of weeks. The next test is on a reminder. The system has me on its list. That was the bit I was missing.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Abdul</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What is happening</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">Continuous self-monitoring via the NHS App, with an annual home re-test and integrated BP self-monitoring. Follow-up appointments account for 54% of NHS outpatient activity nationally; the cohort Abdul represents is the cohort that does not need to be inside that 54%.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Five-yearly NHS Health Check in clinic, with most of the cohort missing most of the cycle, and the cardiovascular events arriving regardless.</div>
        </div>

